# Plan ship gate (required before "done")

When implementing a **plan** or multi-file feature (not tiny one-line fixes):

## Do not mark complete until

1. Read [docs/INTEGRATION_MATRIX.md](docs/INTEGRATION_MATRIX.md) — run **Global baseline** + any **Feature-specific** rows that apply.
2. Add **plan-specific** rows to INTEGRATION_MATRIX if the feature introduces new cross-module paths (config ↔ session, tools ↔ main loop, path normalization, mode switches).
3. Implement **at least one automated test** per new cross-module wiring path (not only happy-path unit tests on absolute tempdirs).
4. Explicitly verify: default config shapes (`workspaceRoot: "."`), session flags vs config flags, dry-run/no-op tools, and git/untracked edge cases when filesystem is involved.

## Definition of done

- `cargo test`, `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy -D warnings` pass.
- Integration matrix rows for this build are checked (document in final summary: which rows ran + any new tests added).
- **Never** treat "all unit tests green" as shippable when the feature touches config, session state, operator modes, or filesystem paths.

## Anti-patterns (caused recent P1s)

- Duplicate jail checks using raw config paths after a normalizing helper already validated.
- Two flags for one behavior (`config.foo.enabled` vs `state.foo_enabled`) without syncing every mutation site (`/mode`, `/new`, presets).
- Tool side effects keyed on `"error"` substring or tool name alone instead of structured result fields (`applied`, etc.).
